item.title: Algorithms
item.description: The algorithms module is designed to teach students about the most common and important algorithms used in computer science. An algorithm is a set of steps that can be followed to solve a specific problem.

item.title: Data Structures
item.description: The data structure module is designed to teach students about the different types of data structures used to store and manipulate data. Data structures are an essential component of computer science and are used in a wide range of applications, from databases and file systems to algorithms and computer graphics.
